1 institution.
2 (h) (e) "Loan application" means a written application for a
3 mortgage loan or home improvement loan.
4 (i) (f) "Loan contract" means a contract for a mortgage loan
5 or home improvement loan.
6 (j) (g) "Mortgage loan" means a loan secured by a mortgage on
7 real property designed for occupancy by 4 or fewer families,
8 including an individual unit of a condominium or cooperative, a
9 refinancing of an existing mortgage loan on real property designed
10 for occupancy by 4 or fewer families involving an increase in the
11 outstanding balance of the principal due, or a loan secured by a
12 junior lien on real property designed for occupancy by 4 or fewer
13 families undertaken for any purpose. Mortgage loan does not include
14 any of the following:
15 (i) Construction financing.
16 (ii) A purchase of an interest in a pool of mortgage loans.
17 (iii) An extension of the maturity of an existing mortgage loan
18 that does not include an increase in the unpaid principal due.
19 (iv) A loan transaction in which the proceeds are not used
20 primarily for a personal, family, or household purpose.
21 (k) (h) "Neighborhood" means either of the following:
22 (i) A census tract as defined by the United States bureau of
23 the census Census Bureau in a federal decennial census, of
24 population, if located within a standard metropolitan statistical
25 area as defined by the United States office of management and
26 budget.Office of Management and Budget.
27 (ii) An area that is designated by a single zip code number
28 under the zoning improvement plan of the United States postal
29 service, Postal Service, if located outside a standard metropolitan
