3 Sec. 2. (1) Except on the basis of written policies or
4 criteria uniformly applied to all neighborhoods within a particular
5 standard metropolitan statistical area or within the county in
6 areas outside a standard metropolitan statistical area, a credit
7 granting institution shall not deny a loan application or vary the
8 interest rate, the term to maturity, the percentage required for a
9 down payment, the application and appraisal procedures, or other
10 terms or conditions of a loan contract for either of the following:
11 (a) Due to racial or ethnic characteristics or trends in the
12 neighborhood in which the real estate is located.
13 (b) Due to the age of the structure on the real estate
14 proposed as security or the age of other structures in the
15 neighborhood in which the real estate is located. This subdivision
16 does not preclude a credit granting institution from considering
17 the physical condition and probable remaining useful life of the
18 structure and all structures within a radius of 750 feet.
19 (2) A policy or criteria used by a credit granting institution
20 is considered to be uniformly applied, even if a credit granting
21 institution grants exceptions to the policy or criteria in favor of
22 a loan applicant in not more than 5% of the loan applications
23 submitted to the credit granting institution.
24 (3) Each loan application shall be individually considered A
25 credit granting institution shall individually consider each loan
26 application on the basis of a factually supportable analysis of the
27 lending risks associated with the proposed loan.
28 (4) A credit granting institution shall not impose a minimum
29 mortgage amount greater than $10,000.00, and a $15,000.00 for a
