1 mortgage loan made before January 1, 2027, $30,000.00 for a
2 mortgage loan made on or after January 1, 2027 and before January
3 1, 2028, and $45,000.00 for a mortgage loan made on or after
4 January 1, 2028. A credit granting institution shall not impose a
5 minimum loan amount of greater than $1,000.00 $1,500.00 for a home
6 improvement loan made before January 1, 2027, $3,000.00 for a home
7 improvement loan made on or after January 1, 2027 and before
8 January 1, 2028, and $4,500.00 for a home improvement loan made on
9 or after January 1, 2028. Beginning January 1, 2032, and by January
10 1 of every fifth year thereafter, the director shall adjust each of
11 the minimum dollar amounts described in this subsection by an
12 amount determined by the state treasurer to reflect the cumulative
13 percentage change in the Consumer Price Index over the 5-year
14 period ending on June 1 of the immediately preceding calendar year,
15 rounded to the nearest multiple of $10.00.
16 (5) A credit granting institution shall not deny an individual
17 an opportunity to submit a loan application. This act shall must
18 not be construed to require a credit union to allow a loan inquiry
19 or application by a person who that is not a member or eligible to
20 be a member of the credit union.
21 (6) A credit granting institution shall provide a person who
22 that makes a loan application for a mortgage loan or home
23 improvement loan that is denied or the terms of which are varied
24 and not accepted by the applicant shall receive from the credit
