3 (7) A credit granting institution, unless otherwise prohibited
4 by law, may charge an application fee uniform as to type of loan.
5 If a credit granting institution includes an appraisal in its
6 written statement of reasons for rejection or variance or collects
7 an application appraisal fee, then upon the request of a person
8 making a loan application that is denied or the terms of which are
9 varied and not accepted by the applicant, a credit granting
10 institution shall provide the person, without additional charge,
11 with a copy of the appraisal made in connection with the loan
12 application. If an application appraisal fee is not collected, the
13 copy may be made usable only for purposes related to this act.
14 Copies A credit granting institution shall provide copies of other
15 completed forms, reports, and correspondence, except a credit
16 report or correspondence pertaining to a credit report, used by the
17 credit granting institution in reaching its decision, shall be
18 provided, on request and without charge, to a person making a loan
19 application that is denied or the terms of which are varied and not
20 accepted by the applicant.
21 (8) Except for an error or omission that is a violation of
22 this act, a credit granting institution is not liable to an
23 applicant or any other person for an error or omission in an
24 appraisal or other supporting documents made available to an
25 applicant.
26 (9) If a person makes a loan inquiry relating to the prospects
27 of obtaining a loan, the credit granting institution shall respond
